## Consequences of Political Division

| Area                  | Consequences                                                                                                  |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Legislative Gridlock** | Reduced efficiency in passing laws; increased use of filibusters and stall tactics ([Binder, 2000](https://doi.org/10.2307/20080888)). |
| **Public Distrust**      | Declining trust in government, media, and scientific institutions; increased political cynicism ([Ladd & Hetherington, 2016](https://brook.gs/3uGQv9X)). |
| **Political Violence**   | Rising justification for violence among partisans; increased risk of domestic unrest ([Kleinfeld, 2020](https://carnegieendowment.org/2020/06/30/should-america-be-worried-about-political-violence-and-what-can-we-do-to-prevent-it-pub-82114)). |
| **Judicial Polarization**| Partisan battles over judicial appointments; erosion of judicial legitimacy ([Hasen, 2019](https://doi.org/10.1146/annurev-polisci-051317-125141)). |
| **Foreign Policy Challenges** | Inconsistent and unilateral foreign policy; reduced credibility with allies ([Beinart, 2008](https://books.google.com)). |

